poetry install
uvicorn main:app --reload

To ensure that your app runs properly,
you should be able to run your local server
using the command uvicorn backend.main:app.

python -m unittest test_main.py

poetry run uvicorn backend.main:app --reload


running your servers:
for the frontend server, run "npm run dev" from within the `frontend` directory
for the backend server, run "uvicorn backend.main:app --reload" from the base directory

poetry install
requirements.txt

npm run dev
poetry run uvicorn backend.main:app --reload
